    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of what the plan covers:\n\n## Plan: Add `extensions/pulseboard/` Channel Plugin\n\n**7 new files, 0 existing files modified.**\n\n### Key findings from codebase exploration\n\n1. **`getChatChannelMeta` is a no-go for `pulseboard`** — it looks up metadata from `CHAT_CHANNEL_ORDER` in `src/channels/ids.ts`, which only includes the 9 built-in channels (telegram, discord, irc, etc.). \"pulseboard\" isn't there. The fix: construct `meta` as an inline object, exactly like `extensions/matrix/src/channel.ts` (lines 92–101) already does for Matrix.\n\n2. **`OutboundDeliveryResult` is not on a public SDK subpath** — it lives at `src/infra/outbound/deliver.ts` and is only used internally by `core.ts`. For the `sendText` stub, the plan uses `createEmptyChannelResult(\"pulseboard\", { messageId })` from the public `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-send-result`, which returns a correctly-typed result without touching internals.\n\n3. **Manifest invariant tests** — the repo enforces that `openclaw.plugin.json:id`, `package.json openclaw.channel.id`, and package name all stay in sync. The plan aligns all three to `\"pulseboard\"` / `\"@openclaw/pulseboard\"`.\n\n### Files to create\n\n| File | Pattern followed |\n|---|---|\n| `package.json` | IRC/Nostr shape, no runtime deps |\n| `openclaw.plugin.json` | Standard empty configSchema |\n| `src/types.ts` | Pure TypeScript interfaces (3 exports) |\n| `src/runtime.ts` | `createPluginRuntimeStore<PluginRuntime>` (Nostr pattern) |\n| `src/channel.ts` | `createChatChannelPlugin` with inline meta + 5 adapters |\n| `index.ts` | `defineChannelPluginEntry` (mirrors IRC exactly) |\n| `setup-entry.ts` | `defineSetupPluginEntry(pulseBoardPlugin)` (one-liner) |",
